    "intro": "Interpretation moves from what the text says to what it means — discerning Asaph's intent in the original context of covenant catastrophe and reading that intent through its canonical horizon. The four movements below follow the psalm's argument structure: lament (74:1–11), creation-confession (74:12–17), and covenant petition (74:18–23), with a final movement on the psalm's theological center of gravity. Where Hebrew vocabulary changes the English shade of meaning, a brief note supplements the exposition.",
